@{
    Layout = "~/Views/Shared/_Layout.cshtml";
    ViewBag.Title = "Sustainable Agriculture – Drip Smart USA";
    ViewBag.MetaDescription = "Grow more food with less water, less land, and fewer inputs. DripSmart irrigation technology supports a more sustainable future for American agriculture.";
}

<section class="page-hero" style="background: linear-gradient(135deg, #0d4a2e 0%, #181F4E 100%);">
    <div class="container page-hero-inner">
        <div class="page-hero-text">
            <nav class="breadcrumb"><a href="/">Home</a> / <a href="/agriculture">Agriculture</a> / <span>Sustainable Agriculture</span></nav>
            <h1>Grow More. Use Less. Leave More Behind.</h1>
            <p>Sustainability isn't a compromise — it's a competitive advantage. DripSmart products help growers produce more food per acre while reducing water use, nutrient runoff, and energy costs.</p>
            <a href="/agriculture/crops" class="btn-primary" style="margin-top:24px;">Explore by Crop</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- The Problem -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="align-items:center;">
            <div>
                <span class="section-eyebrow">The Challenge</span>
                <h2>Agriculture Faces a Water Reckoning</h2>
                <p>Agriculture accounts for roughly 70% of global freshwater withdrawals. In the American West, aquifers are depleting faster than they recharge. In the South, drought frequency is rising. Regulators, lenders, and buyers are all paying closer attention to how farms use water.</p>
                <p style="margin-top:14px;">The farms that thrive in the next decade won't just produce more — they'll produce more efficiently, with verifiable data to prove it.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="benefit-stat-card" style="align-self:start;">
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">70%</span><span class="big-label">of freshwater use is agriculture</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">50%</span><span class="big-label">water reduction possible with drip vs. flood</span></div>
                <div class="big-stat"><span class="big-number">40%</span><span class="big-label">less fertilizer lost to runoff</span></div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- Pillars -->
<section class="section" style="background:var(--blue-pale);">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">Four Pillars</span>
            <h2>How DripSmart Supports Sustainable Farming</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="two-col-layout" style="margin-top:40px; gap:24px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">💧</div>
                <h3>Water Conservation</h3>
                <p>Drip irrigation delivers water directly to the root zone, eliminating the evaporation, surface runoff, and deep percolation that waste 30–50% of water in flood and sprinkler systems. Every drop goes exactly where it's needed.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌱</div>
                <h3>Soil Health</h3>
                <p>Low-volume, high-frequency irrigation maintains consistent soil moisture without over-saturating the profile. This protects soil structure, promotes microbial activity, and reduces compaction — building long-term fertility.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🧪</div>
                <h3>Nutrient Efficiency</h3>
                <p>Fertigation through drip lines puts nutrients directly in the root zone in small, frequent doses. Crops uptake more of what they're given — and nothing leaches into groundwater or runs off into streams.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">⚡</div>
                <h3>Energy Reduction</h3>
                <p>Drip systems operate at low pressure (typically 8–15 PSI), requiring far less pump energy than center-pivot or overhead systems. Less water pumped also means less energy per acre-foot delivered.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

<!-- ESG & Reporting -->
<section class="section">
    <div class="container">
        <div class="section-header centered">
            <span class="section-eyebrow">For Forward-Looking Operations</span>
            <h2>Data You Can Report. Results You Can Prove.</h2>
            <p style="max-width:640px; margin:16px auto 0;">Lenders, food companies, and carbon markets increasingly require documented sustainability metrics. DripSphere OS™ records water applied, fertilizer injected, and system run-time — giving you the data you need.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="three-col-grid" style="margin-top:40px;">
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">📊</div>
                <h3>Water Use Tracking</h3>
                <p>Automatically log every irrigation event — volume, duration, zone, and date. Export reports for lender compliance, water district reporting, or internal benchmarking.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🧾</div>
                <h3>Fertigation Records</h3>
                <p>Every nutrient injection is logged by product, rate, and zone. Useful for nutrient management plans, GAP audits, and agronomic decision-making.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="info-card">
                <div class="info-card-icon">🌍</div>
                <h3>Carbon Footprint Support</h3>
                <p>Reduced water pumping, lower fertilizer use, and precision application all contribute to a smaller carbon footprint — with the records to substantiate it in carbon programs.</p>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="text-center mt-lg">
            <a href="/digital-farming/dripsphere-os" class="btn-primary">See DripSphere OS™ Monitoring</a>
        </div>
    </div>
</section>

